					<article id="post-116" class="post-116 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-programming category-uncategorized">
	<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title">
			<a href="http://bradkovach.com/2012/07/increase-phps-upload-capacity/" title="Permalink to Increase PHP&#8217;s upload capacity" rel="bookmark">Increase PHP&#8217;s upload capacity</a>
		</h1>
	</header>
	<!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">

				
						
			<p>Handy piece of code I use all the time when set up WordPress installation. Change the 30M to whatever you want. 2048M is good for 2 gigabytes.</p><!-- Crayon Syntax Highlighter v2.6.1 -->

